.TH PRETTY_FILES 1 "July 2026" "pretty_files 2.0.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
pretty_files \- lightweight command-line file viewer with syntax highlighting and hexadecimal binary viewer

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B pretty_files
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <PATHS...>

.br

.B pretty_files
.B bare
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <DIRECTORIES...>

.br

.B pretty_files
.B binary
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <FILES...>

.br

.B pretty_files
.B help

.br

.B pretty_files
.B version

.SH DESCRIPTION

.B pretty_files
is a lightweight command-line file viewer written in Rust. It supports
syntax-highlighted text viewing, hexadecimal binary viewing, recursive
directory traversal, optional line numbers, file filtering, and automatic
file headers when displaying multiple files.

Syntax highlighting is automatically selected based on the detected file
type. Files with unsupported or unknown extensions are displayed as plain
text.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B help
Display the help menu.

.TP
.B bare
Print file paths without displaying their contents.
Useful for piping file lists into other commands.

.TP
.B binary
Display binary files as hexadecimal dumps with an ASCII preview.

.TP
.B version
Display the installed version of
.BR pretty_files .

.SH READ MODE

Read mode is the default mode and displays the contents of one or more text
files.

.SS Options

.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-numbers
Display line numbers.

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Recursively search directories for files.

.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Print the file name before displaying its contents.

.TP
.B \-D
Disable automatic debug mode.

Automatic debug mode is enabled automatically when multiple files are
displayed.

.TP
.B \-S
Disable syntax highlighting.

.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ignore " " <PATH>
Ignore a file or path.
This option may be specified multiple times.

.SS Examples

.TP
Display a file:
.B pretty_files main.rs

.TP
Display multiple files:
.B pretty_files main.rs Cargo.toml

.TP
Display line numbers:
.B pretty_files -n src/main.rs

.TP
Display all files recursively:
.B pretty_files -r src/

.TP
Disable syntax highlighting:
.B pretty_files -S file.txt

.TP
Ignore a file:
.B pretty_files -r -i src/lib.rs src/

.TP
Ignore multiple files:
.B pretty_files -r -i src/lib.rs -i src/main.rs src/

.SH BARE MODE

The
.B bare
command prints file paths without displaying file contents.

.SS Synopsis

.B pretty_files bare
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <DIRECTORIES...>

.SS Options

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Recursively list files inside directories.

.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ignore " " <PATH>
Ignore a file or path.
This option may be specified multiple times.

.SS Examples

.TP
List files in a directory:
.B pretty_files bare src/

.TP
List files recursively:
.B pretty_files bare -r src/

.TP
Ignore a file:
.B pretty_files bare -r -i src/lib.rs src/

.TP
Ignore multiple files:
.B pretty_files bare -r -i src/lib.rs -i src/main.rs src/

.TP
Use the output in a shell loop:
.nf
for file in $(pretty_files bare -r src/); do
    cat "$file"
done
.fi

.SH BINARY MODE

The
.B binary
command displays binary files as hexadecimal dumps with a printable ASCII
preview.

.SS Synopsis

.B pretty_files binary
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <FILES...>

.SS Options

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Recursively search directories for files.

.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Print the file name before displaying its contents.

.TP
.B \-D
Disable automatic debug mode.

Automatic debug mode is enabled automatically when multiple files are
displayed.

.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ignore " " <PATH>
Ignore a file or path.
This option may be specified multiple times.

.SS Examples

.TP
Display a binary file:
.B pretty_files binary image.png

.TP
Display an executable:
.B pretty_files binary /bin/ls

.TP
Recursively display binary files:
.B pretty_files binary -r build/

.TP
Ignore a file:
.B pretty_files binary -r -i build/cache.bin build/

.TP
Ignore multiple files:
.B pretty_files binary -r -i cache.bin -i test.bin build/

.SH NOTES

.TP
Automatic debug mode is enabled when displaying multiple files.
Use
.B \-D
to disable it.

.TP
The
.B \-r
option expects directories as input.

.TP
Text files with unknown or unsupported extensions are displayed as plain
text.

.TP
Binary mode displays data as hexadecimal values alongside printable ASCII
characters.

.SH DEPENDENCIES

.TP
.B syntect
Provides syntax highlighting and language detection.

.TP
.B walkdir
Provides recursive directory traversal.

